oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Highlander Fling, Vol. 6, No. 4
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Highlander Fling special issue on the Farm Program. Topics include farmers unions, upcoming bills that might affect farmers, and examples of successful cooperatives across the state.

The Highlander Fling was the Highlander Folk School's newsletter. First published in December 1933, the Fling detailed activities and goings-on at Highlander was well as educational programs, articles from staff and participants, and calls to action.
